        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "Notes and context\n- The three stepwise pKa values correspond to the triprotic deprotonation of citric acid (H3L → H2L− → HL2− → L3−). Values vary with ionic strength and temperature, as reflected by the measured logKassoc ranges above.\n- The ordering pKa1 < pKa2 < pKa3 is consistent with progressively harder deprotonation of a polyprotic carboxylic acid; increased ionic strength tends to stabilize charged species, often shifting apparent pKa.",
